result.name: Carrianna ChiuChow Cuisine Restaurant

reviews.text: Perhaps the only traditional restaurant in HK specializing in Chiu Chow cuisines. The restaurant has had a long history and has been operating in the current locations for nearly 30 years. The shark fin soup is the restaurant signature dish as well as cold crabs and goose legs. Food is generally prepared in good standard and the service is fine. Apart from the highly priced shark fin soup and the seafoods, the restaurant is worth a visit if you wish to try the traditional Chiu Chow way of cooking.
Great food & ambience.  Friendly staff. Attentive service.

Solid Chiu Chow style food open for lunch and dinner. Since it's located in Wan Chai, their Mon-Fri lunches are actually quite busy with office workers coming in for their regular meals, so I'd recommend either making a reservation or coming in earlier at around 11 to 11:30am. Their service is more old-school and can be spotty at times. Their dimsum is fairly priced and sticks to Chiu Chow roots for sure. The decor and environment is quite old-school and in need of a reno.

Very friendly and efficient staff. Food was excellent, even some of the more unusual dishes. Very traditional style and a bit too much emphasis on shark fin for my liking.
The deep fried pork rolled in cabbage leaves were great. I enjoyed my share of an oyster omelette even though it sounded odd.
I have not tasted quality of this cuisine at the restaurant.

Traditional Chiu Chow restaurant.  Nice food. Good service. Mediocre price. Recommended.
